---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import PNotes from "../components/PNotes.astro";
const { externalImage } = Astro.props;
---

<p-slide class="cover-internal">
  <h3 style="margin-block-end: 0.5em;">Not only horizontal direction!</h3>
  <span style="font-size: 8rem;">
    {
      externalImage ? (
        <Image
          class="alter-image-size"
          src={externalImage}
          alt="alien post"
          style="--image-start-size: 2.3em;margin-block-start: 1rem;"
        />
      ) : (
        "🧧"
      )
    }
  </span>
  <PNotes>
    Traditionally, Japanese, Korean, and Chinese (including Vietnamese in the
    past) have used vertical writing, with columns running from top to bottom
    and ordered from right to left. While horizontal writing is now common in
    all these languages, vertical writing remains prevalent in Japanese,
    especially in manga, novels, and some traditional context
  </PNotes>
</p-slide>
<p-slide autoplay timing="600" timing-fragment="700" class="cover-internal">
  <h3 style="margin-block-end: 0.5em;">Guess what?</h3>
  <p-fragment>
    CSS help us to <span class="cover-all">write vertically</span>
  </p-fragment>
  <p-fragment style="margin-block-start: 0.3em;" timing-fragment="700">
    with <span style="writing-mode: vertical-rl" class="cover-red-all"
      >writing-mode</span
    > property
  </p-fragment>
</p-slide>
<p-slide>
  <h4 style="margin-block-end: 0.5em" class="center">Let&#39;s Code 👨‍💻</h4>
  <pre
    class="small-line"
    data-label-file="inset.css">
 <code is:raw style="font-size: .8em" class="language-scss"> 
    .vertical-left-aligned {
      writing-mode: vertical-lr;
    }</code>
</pre>
  <div
    style="font-size: 0.8em; writing-mode: vertical-lr; margin-inline-start: 1em; margin-block: auto"
  >
    我家没有电脑。
  </div>
</p-slide>
<p-slide>
  <h4 style="margin-block-end: 0.5em" class="center">Let&#39;s Code 👨‍💻</h4>
  <pre
    class="small-line"
    data-label-file="inset.css">
 <code is:raw style="font-size: .8em" class="language-scss"> 
    .vertical-left-invert-aligned {
      writing-mode: sideways-lr;
    }</code>
</pre>
  <div
    style="font-size: 0.8em; writing-mode: sideways-lr; margin-inline-end: 1em; margin-block: auto"
  >
    我家没有电脑。
  </div>
</p-slide>
<p-slide>
  <h4 style="margin-block-end: 0.5em" class="center">Let&#39;s Code 👨‍💻</h4>
  <pre
    class="small-line"
    data-label-file="inset.css">
 <code is:raw style="font-size: .8em" class="language-scss"> 
    .vertical-right-aligned {
      writing-mode: vertical-rl;
